Here is my solution for finding the tall males driving the blue honda with the semi-known licencse plate. I found awk quite suitable.<p><pre><code>  awk &#x27;BEGIN {RS=&quot;

&quot;; FS=&quot;
&quot;} $1 ~ /L337.*9$/ && $2 ~ /Honda/ && $3 ~ /Blue/ && $5 ~ /6&#x27;\&#x27;&#x27;/ {print $4}&#x27; vehicles | cut -d&#x27; &#x27; -f2,3
</code></pre>
Edit: And to find the intersection between the SkyMiles members and the members of the Museum of Bash History, I used fgrep:<p><pre><code>  grep -Fxf Delta_SkyMiles Museum_of_Bash_History</code></pre>
